reviews.title: Easy
reviews.comment: App works well. Those of you that can\'t close the app on DROID platform, try the middle button. Not the back or menu buttons.
reviews.author: George Samon

reviews.title: Crashes
reviews.comment: Force closes every time I click claim to reimburse.
reviews.author: Steven Goff

reviews.title: Force closes
reviews.comment: Can find claims I need to request reimbursement for,  but it forces closes when I try and enter.   This is on my galaxy nexus.   If this is fixed,  will be a good ap.
reviews.author: Aaron Stone

reviews.title: Love this app!
reviews.comment: I am able to manage my acct via my phone. App is easy to use.

reviews.title: App sucks balls
reviews.comment: Every time I try to check my claims it force closes.

reviews.title: Can\'t back out
reviews.comment: Can\'t exit the app and it locks up if you try a second pic
reviews.author: michael versak

reviews.title: Motorola ATRIX HD
reviews.comment: I have a similar model to the Droid. This app crashes when taking pictures or uploading pictures, but I\'ve found the solution is to do the upload quickly, then it doesn\'t crash! I recommend always submitting the claim without attached docs, first, so it\'s saved. Then you can upload the docs without worrying about the app crashing.  I love that I can just take pictures and not have to scan!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great app
reviews.comment: So much easier
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Very handy
reviews.comment: Very nicely done app except I cant exit it. I have to hit home and then force close it. Would also be nice if it could remember your password or at least the option to. I have a password on my phone already.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Help!
reviews.comment: It force closes every time I try to take or upload a picture of a receipt.

reviews.title: Great if it would remember my password
reviews.comment: I really like that I can just take a picture of my receipt to send in rather than waiting to get to a scanner/copier at work to make a PDF. Would be better if it always remembered my complex 16-char password.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: I love it! No more waiting to scan the receipts. Took the picture and uploaded. Claim is now in review. Less than 5 minutes to do it all!

reviews.comment: I love being notified to keep my receipt when I use my health card and uploading it with my phone. What a time saver!

reviews.title: Core function doesn\'t work
reviews.comment: I downloaded the app so I could view and pay a claim, which is probably why others use this app too. I can see a list of my claims, but when I click on one, the app crashes immediately. Also, I can\'t exit the application the way I do from EVERY OTHER App... by hitting the back button from the main screen! Please fix this.
